IMPORTANT NOTES

I. Concerning the application

	1. for the approval of the business trip, the procedures in force at the Institute must be followed.

	2. in your own interest, do not start the business trip until you have received the written order or approval.

	Failure to do so may result in the loss of any claims that may exist in the event of an official or work-related injury.

	3. if the trip is started one or more days earlier (or the return trip is made later) for private reasons, then the earlier arrival (or later departure) would no longer be substantially influenced by the professional connection, but by the private interests.

	In such a case, there would no longer be a direct route to (or from) the work-related assignment, with the consequence that this route would not be covered by the statutory accident insurance. 4.

	4. in deviation from the BRKG, only 2nd class may be used for rail travel in the research association.

	5. the use of rental cars must be justified.

	6. For travel by means of transport other than those specified in S 4 BRKG, a distance allowance will be granted.

	There is no liability for material damage.

	7. if there is a considerable official interest in the use of the private car S 5 Para. 2 BRKG, a separate application must be submitted to the Director of the Institute.

	8. information on daily and overnight rates can be found at www.fv-berlin.de/intern/download-formulare-1.

II. about accounting

	1. the business trip statement must be prepared within a preclusive period of 6 months.

	The preclusive period begins on the day after the end of the business trip. 2.

	2. original receipts for expenses (travel, conference fees, incidental expenses, hotel, cab, etc.) must be attached to the statement.

	3. for business trips abroad, the date and time of the border crossing (in the case of air travel, the time of landing in the country of destination) must be stated.

	4. for increased overnight expenses (more than 70e within the country; higher than overnight rates abroad), a justification must be attached.

	5. meals received free of charge must be indicated.

	This includes meals included in the conference fee or provided on the plane.

	The same applies to overnight stays received free of charge.